# RANK 1 ★ — Specialized AMC/Maintenance Business

```
SCORE: 22/25 (EASY: 5 · SAFE: 5 · SCALE: 4 · SPEED: 5 · INDIA ADV: 3)
```

### 🟢 Easy Entry · ⚡ Fast Revenue · Score: 22/25

**What it is:** Providing Annual Maintenance Contracts for ONE specific product category — water purifiers, CCTV systems, solar panels, AC units, or UPS/inverters. You service all brands, collect yearly fees upfront, and deliver scheduled maintenance visits. India has crores of installed devices whose original sellers disappeared — customers are DESPERATE for reliable maintenance.

**How it works:** You sign up apartment societies and offices on annual contracts (₹2,000–8,000/year per device). Customer pays UPFRONT for 12 months. You provide 2–4 scheduled visits per year plus emergency support. Your cost per visit: ₹300–500 (parts + travel). Rest is profit. Recurring revenue that renews every year.

**Players:** Urban Company (big, marketplace — you're competing differently: direct, niche, local), brand service centers (only service their own brand), individual repairmen (unreliable, no contracts). No organized multi-brand AMC provider exists in most cities for most device categories.

**Best Model:** Subscription 🔄 (annual AMC) + Service Fee 🔧 (emergency calls outside AMC)

**Revenue Speed:** ⚡ Fast — first paying customer within 1–2 weeks. Revenue from Day 1.

**Revenue Ideas:**
- Base: AMC subscriptions (₹2,000–8,000/year per device)
- Emergency calls outside AMC: ₹500–1,500 per visit
- Spare parts markup: 30–50% on genuine parts
- Cross-sell: if you service their RO, offer AC service too (same customer, 2x revenue)
- Referral bonus: ₹200 off next renewal for every referral that converts

**Challenges:**
- ⚙ Technician reliability — if your person doesn't show up on time, customer cancels
- 📈 Unorganized competition from local repair guys (but they don't offer contracts)
- 🧠 Must learn the specific device category thoroughly
- ⚙ Spare parts sourcing for multiple brands
- 📈 Customer expects instant response for emergencies

**Common Mistake:** Using cheap spare parts to save ₹200 per visit. Cheap RO filters mean bad-tasting water in 3 months → customer blames you → cancels AMC → tells 10 neighbors. Original/quality parts ONLY. The ₹200 saved costs you ₹20,000 in lost renewals.

**One-liner:** Pick one device category, sign societies on yearly contracts, collect upfront, service quarterly — the safest recurring revenue business with almost zero competition from organized players.

**Why it's SAFE:**
- Demand is GUARANTEED — every water purifier, AC, CCTV NEEDS service
- Revenue is UPFRONT — customer pays ₹2,499 before you do any work
- Recession-proof — people don't cancel water purifier maintenance in a downturn
- Low capital — ₹10,000 toolkit + ₹15,000 spare parts inventory = you're in business
- Renewals — 70–80% of AMC customers renew every year if service was good

**India Advantage:** India has crores of devices with broken warranty and disappeared sellers. Urban Company is marketplace only (doesn't employ technicians). NO organized, branded, multi-brand AMC company exists in most Indian cities. First mover in your city wins.

**Step-by-Step to First ₹:**

```
Day 1–3:     Pick ONE device: water purifier, CCTV, AC, solar panel, or UPS.
             (Water purifier recommended — highest volume, easiest to learn.)

Day 4–7:     Watch 20 YouTube tutorials on RO/UV servicing.
             Practice on your own + 3 friends' purifiers for free.
             Buy basic toolkit: ₹5,000. Spare parts stock: ₹15,000.

Day 8–10:    Print 200 pamphlets: "Annual Water Purifier Service — All Brands
             — ₹2,499/year — 2 visits + filter change + emergency support."
             Include your WhatsApp number.

Day 11–15:   Visit 5 apartment societies. Meet security guard → ask for
             RWA secretary's number → call → request 5 minutes at next
             RWA meeting OR just put pamphlets in mailboxes.

Day 16–21:   First 5–10 sign-ups from pamphlets. Collect ₹2,499 each via UPI.
             Schedule first service visits. Go in uniform (branded t-shirt: ₹300).

Day 22–30:   Service first batch. Take before/after photos. Send "service
             completed" WhatsApp with photos. Ask for Google review.
             Target: 30 AMC customers by Day 30 = ₹74,970 collected.

Month 2–3:   Scale to 5 more societies. Target: 100 customers.
             Hire first technician (₹12,000–15,000/month salary).

Month 4–6:   200+ customers. Revenue: ₹5L+ collected (annual).
             Add second device category (e.g., CCTV for same societies).

Year 1:      500+ customers. 2–3 technicians.
             Revenue: ₹12–15L/year. Renewing customers = predictable.

Year 2:      1,000+ customers. Add more device categories.
             Revenue: ₹25–40L/year.
```

**Keep In Mind:**
- ✅ UNIFORM YOUR TECHNICIANS — branded t-shirt + ID card + shoe covers = instant trust when entering homes. ₹5,000 investment for 10 uniforms changes everything.
- ✅ WhatsApp reminder BEFORE every visit — "Hi Mrs. Sharma, your RO service is on Thursday 10 AM. Technician Ravi will arrive. Please keep the area accessible."
- ✅ Send service completion photo on WhatsApp — TDS meter reading before and after shows the filter change actually worked. Visual proof = zero complaints.
- ✅ Track every customer in Google Sheets or simple CRM — name, address, device brand, filter type, last service date, next service due. This is your business engine.
- ⚠️ Don't expand to second device category before mastering first — become known as "the RO service guy" before adding CCTV. Specialization builds reputation.
- ⚠️ Never miss a scheduled appointment — one no-show loses a customer forever. Over-staff rather than under-staff.
- ⚠️ Carry extra common parts — show up, diagnose, fix in ONE visit. "I'll come back with the part" is how you lose customers to the local repair guy.

