**What it is:** Building AI-powered solutions — chatbots, document processors, content automation, data analytics dashboards, voice agents — for US/EU businesses. You charge in dollars ($2,000–10,000/project), build using Indian talent (₹15L/year developer vs $150K/year in US). The time zone gap becomes an advantage: client sends brief at 6 PM EST, you work normal Indian hours, client wakes up to completed delivery. Magic.

**How it works:** Pick ONE AI service niche (not "we do AI"). Build a demo. Cold outreach on LinkedIn to US/EU decision-makers in your target industry. Land 2–3 clients at $2,000–5,000/month retainer each. Deliver overnight. Scale by hiring Indian developers.

**Players:** US AI agencies charge $10,000–50,000/project. Indian IT giants (TCS, Infosys) serve Fortune 500 but ignore SMBs. Individual freelancers on Upwork compete on price. YOU position as premium-but-affordable specialist (not cheap generalist).

